 Purchase the metal and we will get the pieces made for you...<br>
<br>
(2)Blue Diamond Electrum Earring ( 0.1 WT, +15 MANA, +6 SV COLD, +11 SV DISEASE, +6 SV FIRE, +4 SV MAGIC, +11 SV POISON)<br>
 <br>
Golden Blue Diamond Pendant ( 0.1 WT, +20 MANA, +11 SV COLD, +6 SV DISEASE, +11 SV FIRE, +4 SV MAGIC, +6 SV POISON)<br>
 <br>
Platinum Blue Diamond Tiara ( 0.1 WT, +25 MANA, +8 SV COLD, +8 SV DISEASE, +8 SV FIRE, +8 SV MAGIC, +8 SV POISON) <br>
<br>
(2)Velium Blue Diamond Bracelet ( +30 MANA, +11 SV COLD, +9 SV DISEASE, +9 SV FIRE, +9 SV MAGIC, +9 SV POISON) <br>
<br>
Golden Diamond Mask ( 0.1 WT, +10 SV COLD, +5 SV DISEASE, +10 SV FIRE, +3 SV MAGIC, +5 SV POISON) <br>
<br>
(2)Velium Diamond Wedding Ring ( 0.1 WT, +8 SV COLD, +8 SV DISEASE, +8 SV FIRE, +8 SV MAGIC, +8 SV POISON) <br>
<br>
Crown of the Froglock King ( 0.5 WT, 12 AC, +20 SV COLD, +20 SV FIRE) <br>
<br>
If we want to start trying the larger targets and higher end zones resist gear is a must.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub64.ezboard.com/utankagespankage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tankagespankage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/12/02 9:29:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub64.ezboard.com/fchaoticnightsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Resist Gear</span><hr size=1> Resist gear: We need to work harder on getting a full set of resist gear for everyone. There is NO WAY we can start moving into higher end zones such as ToV without it. I have used diamonds and BD’s that have dropped in raids along with guild funds to get most of you started on a set. Blue Diamond are now selling for 500pp in NFP, the metals for different pieces can run from 10pp to 250pp. This is not expensive when compared to the drops we will be able to acquire in these higher zones. Spend a day in Seb or similar zone, you will easily make a few hundred pp if not more. I have listed above the pieces we need to be able to advance on to other raid zones. Please start working on this, it is not that tough of a request and it is really holding us back. If you encounter a problem or a reason that you can not put together a set of resist gear please send myself or Imas a /tell and we will try to help you. People are not taking this serious enough.<br>
<br>
My goal is for EVERYONE to have a full set in 2 weeks. I am going to schedule a ToV raid 2 weeks from this weekend. If you do not have the resist gear by then, you will not be going. For people level 55+ min resists UNBUFFED is 100 MR, FR, and CR. For Levels 52-54 your min resists will be min 120 UNBUFFED. This is done for the simple reason that these dragons have a fierce AE, if your resists are not high enough we spend more time rezzing you than we do actually fighting. Another major factor of ToV is levels, the difference between level 59 and 60 when it comes to resisting AE’s is huge. With every level you advance you have a greater chance of resisting or taking less damage per hit. For an example of why I am stressing this, in HoT (Halls of Testing) there are red and white wurms, besides many other creatures, These are all level 60+, their melee damage from what I remember as being main tank there was around 250 with defensive disco up, the majority of the damage I took was from the 450 dmg AE that it cast maybe every 20 seconds. <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub64.ezboard.com/bchaoticnights.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=imas>imas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/12/02 8:47:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub64.ezboard.com/fchaoticnightsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Resist Gear</span><hr size=1> More Specific...  the AEs are rain damage in a sense.. once the first one lands 2 more will follow..  so the 300-450dmg AE's turn out being over 1200 damage every 30sec if your resists are not up to par.   Granted, if your a casters you will not be in range of the AE's...  you still need resist, you will have to be in range of the AE to cast on the mob...  <br>
<br>
Please take the resists serious..  we do want to start going to ToV and other zones such as Sshissar Temple...  but first thing is first..  resists..   <p>Imas Illusion                        
Lead Officer</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub64.ezboard.com/uboodeeda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Boodeeda</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/14/02 12:06:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub64.ezboard.com/fchaoticnightsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Resist Gear</span><hr size=1> Damn, I just took another look at my stats without buffs.....it's sad.<br>
<br>
I'll need a set of resist geat MINUS the mask please<br>
<br>
And even if I get a whole set, my resists will be still bad I think <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub64.ezboard.com/usynnerelite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SynnerElite</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/15/02 6:21:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub64.ezboard.com/fchaoticnightsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Resist Gear</span><hr size=1> I already have my 2 Rings, 1 bracer, and a BD to use, I can also buy a ton of metal, I got about 5.5k in my bank right now to throw towards resist gear easy.  Just set it up with me and we'll buy metal/Diamonds for my resist gear.<br>
<br>
Ailwien Synner<br>
Outrider of the 55th season <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub64.ezboard.com/uboodeeda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Boodeeda</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/19/02 1:54:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub64.ezboard.com/fchaoticnightsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> My resist gear</span><hr size=1> Well, even though I only have 2 platinum diamond rings, gold diamond mask, and a blue diamond golden velium necklace, I did pretty good resisting the dragons in WW that other day.  It's AE breath was only hitting me for like around 200 damage each time, which is very good I think.  The thurg quest armor helps also.  We can do more dragons easily I think with full groups of 2.  I'm sure we wouldn't have any problems with getting our faction back pretty quickly neither.  Tankage has a ton of helms to give out and we always hit Kael anyways. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub64.ezboard.com/bchaoticnights.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=keiara>keiara</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://home.swbell.net/andyp007/Misc/Kei.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(9/14/02 9:45:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub64.ezboard.com/fchaoticnightsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My resist gear</span><hr size=1> Well if this offer is stilll open Keiara will need some, pendant, tiara and a bracer and the rings should be good. Will try to save up for the metal...anyone know something i can camp for BD's? <p>http://home.swbell.net/andyp007/Kei.htm</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub64.ezboard.com/utankagespankage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tankagespankage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(9/18/02 6:24:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub64.ezboard.com/fchaoticnightsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My resist gear</span><hr size=1> Yes this is still open. I have a few BD's and about 15 or so regular diamonds in the bank that I have collected on raids and that people have donated. Knee and Rek are both at max JC I believe so just pick up the metals, let me know what ya need and schedule something with either of them 2 to get it made.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub64.ezboard.com/usynnerelite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SynnerElite</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(10/15/02 11:20:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub64.ezboard.com/fchaoticnightsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ???</span><hr size=1> I can't figure out where the hell my IGS is... still have all my other resist gear tho... might need to go farming them sometime soon.  Down in The Ho.... er, Hole... Yeah... that's it....  Mebbe it's on my chanter...<br>
